title: Two Tactics of Social-Democracy in the Democratic Revolution
creator: Vladimir Ilyich Lenin
description: LibriVox recording of Two Tactics of Social-Democracy in the Democratic Revolution, by Vladimir Ilyich Lenin. Read by Christian Pecaut. In the heat of the failed 1905 revolution in Russia, Lenin here contrasts the precision of the Bolshevik political program and tactics with various inconsistent and servile factions within the Russian Social-Democratic Labor Party. (Summary by Christian Pecaut) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books, or to become a volunteer reader, please visit LibriVox.org. M4B format available
